==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chass
<hw>Chas`s⟦eacute⟧"</hw> <pr>(sh⟦adot⟧s`s⟦asl⟧")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F., fr. <ets>chass⟦eacute⟧</ets>, p. p. of <ets>chasser</ets> to
chase.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A movement in dancing, as across or to
the right or left.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A gliding step in dancing in which one foot is kept
in front of the other while moving.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chasse</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Chass
<hw>Chas`s⟦eacute⟧"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <fld>(Dancing)</fld> <def>To
